Reasoning: The paper proposes a machine learning model that learns from data and domain knowledge to improve healthcare decision support systems. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of explainability concepts also suggests a focus on interpretability and transparency in the model, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the use of data from different doctors and patients suggests a focus on data management and analysis, which could fall under the category of databases (cs.DB).
